{{Expand language|1=en|time=2020-07-13T19:37:57+00:00}}
'''路径依赖'''（{{lang-en|Path dependence}}）是指给定条件下人们的决策选择受制于其过去的决策，即使过去的境况可能已经过时。<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dailykos.com/story/2007/06/15/346883/-Our-Love-Of-Sewers-A-Lesson-in-Path-Dependence|title=Our Love of Sewers: A Lesson in Path Dependence|author=Dave Praeger|publisher=Daily Kos|date=2007年6月15日|accessdate=2014年7月29日|archive-date=2014年7月29日|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140729183000/http://www.dailykos.com/story/2007/06/15/346883/-Our-Love-Of-Sewers-A-Lesson-in-Path-Dependence|dead-url=no}}</ref>路径依赖被[[经济学|经济学]]采用，以解释在制度变迁中偶然性的作用，以及制度变迁对[[初值|初值]]的敏感性。

在经济学和[[社会科学|社会科学]]中，路径依赖可以指某一特定时刻的结果，或者指过程的长期平衡。通常而言，路径依赖有广义和狭义之分。广义泛指历史因素的影响作用；<ref>{{cite book |last1=Liebowitz |first1= S. |last2=Margolis |first2= Stephen |title= Encyclopedia of Law and Economics |year= 2000 |isbn= 978-1-85898-984-6 |page= 981 |quote= Most generally, path dependence means that where we go next depends not only on where we are now, but also upon where we have been.}}</ref> 而狭义是指制度的自我加强，即初始时的细微差异会被放大，从而不成比例地引发了后来的境况，并且在强形式下，这一历史影响是无效率的。<ref name="LMTypes">{{cite book |last1= Liebowitz |first1= S. |last2= Margolis |first2= S. |editor1-first= Boudewijn |editor1-last= Bouckaert |editor2-first= Gerrit |editor2-last= De Geest |title= Encyclopedia of Law and Economics, Volume I. The History and Methodology of Law and Economics |url= http://encyclo.findlaw.com/0770book.pdf |accessdate= 2010-05-20 |date= September 2000 |publisher= Edward Elgar |location= Cheltenham |isbn= 978-1-85898-984-6 |page= 985 |quote= path dependence can be weak (the efficiency of the chosen path is tied with some alternatives), semi-strong, (the chosen path is not the best but not worth fixing, or strong (the chosen path is highly inefficient, but we are unable to correct it). |archive-date= 2010-12-06 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20101206033616/http://encyclo.findlaw.com/0770book.pdf |dead-url= no }}</ref>

广义的路径依赖，即“历史有影响作用”，在解释效果上其真理性显得无关紧要，因为凡事都有原因，而且在这些领域，早先境况的直接影响并不显著。<ref>{{cite journal |author= Bellaïche, Joël |year=  |title= On the path-dependence of economic growth |journal= Journal of Mathematical Economics |volume= 46 |issue= 2 |page= 178 |url= http://www.math.columbia.edu/~jbellaic/growth.pdf |doi= 10.1016/j.jmateco.2009.11.002 |deadurl= yes |archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20100624073123/http://www.math.columbia.edu/~jbellaic/growth.pdf |archivedate= 2010-06-24 }} 标准的经济增长率尺度是路径依赖的，而对历史依赖的现象在短期（10年、20年）可被忽略，但在长期比较中则不可忽略。</ref>相较而言，狭义的概念更具解释力。

虽然[[QWERTY鍵盤|QWERTY鍵盤]]是被有意设计成限制打字速度的<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.smithsonianmag.com/arts-culture/fact-of-fiction-the-legend-of-the-qwerty-keyboard-49863249/|title=Fact of Fiction? The Legend of the QWERTY Keyboard|last=|first=|date=|work=Smithsonian|access-date=2017-11-09|language=en|archive-date=2019-05-07|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190507194216/https://www.smithsonianmag.com/arts-culture/fact-of-fiction-the-legend-of-the-qwerty-keyboard-49863249/|dead-url=no}}</ref>
，但在普及程度上相对其它较晚出现的键盘一直具有压倒性优势<ref>{{cite web |last1=Harford |first1=Tim |title=How did the qwerty keyboard become so popular? |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/business-47460499 |accessdate=2019-10-16 |language=en |date=2019-04-24 |archive-date=2019-10-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191006095550/https://www.bbc.com/news/business-47460499 |dead-url=no }}</ref>，是路径依赖的一个典型例子。國際[[標準軌|標準軌]]寬是1435毫米，同樣是一個例子<ref>{{Cite book|title=經濟史的趣味|last=|first=|publisher=|year=|isbn=|location=|pages=}}</ref>。

因为路径依赖的存在，学习一门学科的最简单方式，往往要从这门学科的历史开始。[[恩格斯|恩格斯]]就曾经说，学习哲学的最佳方式就是学习它的历史。{{fact}}

